Hottinger was the author of a variety of learned theological works, the principal
                    of which are Historia ecclesiastica, 9 vols., 1651-67;
                        Thesaurus philologicusseu
                        clavisScriptural, originally published in 1649;
                        Etymologicon orientale,sire
                        Lexiconharmonicumheptaglotton, 1661. He also wrote a Hebrew and a Chaldee grammar.
